## CRITICAL NOTES

**Privacy:** generation logs contain user prompts. Add a
project-level setting: `enableGenerationLogging: boolean`
defaulting to true. Show users what's being logged in settings.
In the future when you have multiple users, make logs
only visible to the project owner.

**Thinking content storage:** storing thinkingContent.slice(0, 2000)
captures the most useful part (Claude's reasoning about renderer
choice, scene structure, etc) without bloating the DB.
The thinking block is often the most valuable signal — it shows
exactly why Claude made a choice that the user then rejected.

**Quality score computation:** run computeQualityScore() lazily
(when a log is updated with userAction) not eagerly (on all logs
at once). Add a background job to score any logs older than 1 hour
that still have null quality_score — catches cases where the
frontend failed to report the user action.

**The AI analysis endpoint:** this is Claude analyzing its own
outputs. Use extended thinking for this call — the reasoning about
why certain patterns lead to rejections is itself valuable and
should be shown in the UI. Budget 8000 thinking tokens so it
can reason carefully through the logs before responding.

**Start small:** instrument just the Scene Maker agent first.
Once you have 20-30 logs with quality signals, run the first
analysis query. The insights will tell you exactly what to
improve in the rules. This is a tighter feedback loop than
any amount of upfront prompt engineering.
```